So too the merces, like the pretium, must be certa and vera, but need not be iusta, understanding these terms in the senses already given to them under Tit. 233 nor, finally, need the letter be dominus os that which he lets (Dig. 19. 2. 7 ; ib. 9pr. and 6); else subletting would have been impossible.

(a) Locatio conductio operarum, the letting by one (locator) oi his services only to another (conductor), as in all contracts ol free service.
